# Terminal Persistence

- Prefer reusing an existing visible terminal instead of spawning disposable runs when practical.
- Do not intentionally kill or replace a user-visible terminal unless the user explicitly asks.
- For long-running jobs, prefer a terminal workflow that can remain visible after the agent turn ends.
- Before starting a new training or server process, explain whether it will stay attached or run in a managed background session.
- If a managed background session is required, tell the user it may not remain as a visible IDE terminal and offer a persistent alternative.
- When the user wants a persistent page-visible terminal, prefer preparing the command/script and asking to run it in the existing terminal, or reuse the user's current terminal when safe.
